            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Kings.9:1-10:29",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Kings%209%3A1-10%3A29%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22subhead-sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Response%20to%20Solomon%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Solomon%20finished%20building%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20royal%20palace.%20He%20completed%20everything%20he%20had%20planned%20to%20do.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20appeared%20to%20Solomon%20a%20second%20time%2C%20as%20he%20had%20done%20before%20at%20Gibeon.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20him%2C%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20have%20heard%20your%20prayer%20and%20your%20petition.%20I%20have%20set%20this%20Temple%20apart%20to%20be%20holy%26%23x2014%3Bthis%20place%20you%20have%20built%20where%20my%20name%20will%20be%20honored%20forever.%20I%20will%20always%20watch%20over%20it%2C%20for%20it%20is%20dear%20to%20my%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAs%20for%20you%2C%20if%20you%20will%20follow%20me%20with%20integrity%20and%20godliness%2C%20as%20David%20your%20father%20did%2C%20obeying%20all%20my%20commands%2C%20decrees%2C%20and%20regulations%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3Ethen%20I%20will%20establish%20the%20throne%20of%20your%20dynasty%20over%20Israel%20forever.%20For%20I%20made%20this%20promise%20to%20your%20father%2C%20David%3A%20%26%23x2018%3BOne%20of%20your%20descendants%20will%20always%20sit%20on%20the%20throne%20of%20Israel.%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BBut%20if%20you%20or%20your%20descendants%20abandon%20me%20and%20disobey%20the%20commands%20and%20decrees%20I%20have%20given%20you%2C%20and%20if%20you%20serve%20and%20worship%20other%20gods%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3Ethen%20I%20will%20uproot%20Israel%20from%20this%20land%20that%20I%20have%20given%20them.%20I%20will%20reject%20this%20Temple%20that%20I%20have%20made%20holy%20to%20honor%20my%20name.%20I%20will%20make%20Israel%20an%20object%20of%20mockery%20and%20ridicule%20among%20the%20nations.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20though%20this%20Temple%20is%20impressive%20now%2C%20all%20who%20pass%20by%20will%20be%20appalled%20and%20will%20gasp%20in%20horror.%20They%20will%20ask%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWhy%20did%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20do%20such%20terrible%20things%20to%20this%20land%20and%20to%20this%20Temple%3F%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAnd%20the%20answer%20will%20be%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BBecause%20his%20people%20abandoned%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20their%20God%2C%20who%20brought%20their%20ancestors%20out%20of%20Egypt%2C%20and%20they%20worshiped%20other%20gods%20instead%20and%20bowed%20down%20to%20them.%20That%20is%20why%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20brought%20all%20these%20disasters%20on%20them.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESolomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Agreement%20with%20Hiram%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20took%20Solomon%20twenty%20years%20to%20build%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%20and%20his%20own%20royal%20palace.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20that%20time%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe%20gave%20twenty%20towns%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Galilee%20to%20King%20Hiram%20of%20Tyre.%20(Hiram%20had%20previously%20provided%20all%20the%20cedar%20and%20cypress%20timber%20and%20gold%20that%20Solomon%20had%20requested.)%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20when%20Hiram%20came%20from%20Tyre%20to%20see%20the%20towns%20Solomon%20had%20given%20him%2C%20he%20was%20not%20at%20all%20pleased%20with%20them.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20kind%20of%20towns%20are%20these%2C%20my%20brother%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20asked.%20So%20Hiram%20called%20that%20area%20Cabul%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bworthless%26%23x201D%3B)%2C%20as%20it%20is%20still%20known%20today.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20Hiram%20paid%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E9%3A14a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EFor%20Hiram%20had%20paid.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Solomon%209%2C000%20pounds%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E9%3A14b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E120%26%23xA0%3Btalents%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B4%2C000%20kilograms%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20gold.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESolomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Many%20Achievements%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20account%20of%20the%20forced%20labor%20that%20King%20Solomon%20conscripted%20to%20build%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%2C%20the%20royal%20palace%2C%20the%20supporting%20terraces%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E9%3A15%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20millo%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%209%3A24.%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20wall%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20the%20cities%20of%20Hazor%2C%20Megiddo%2C%20and%20Gezer.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3E(Pharaoh%2C%20the%20king%20of%20Egypt%2C%20had%20attacked%20and%20captured%20Gezer%2C%20killing%20the%20Canaanite%20population%20and%20burning%20it%20down.%20He%20gave%20the%20city%20to%20his%20daughter%20as%20a%20wedding%20gift%20when%20she%20married%20Solomon.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Solomon%20rebuilt%20the%20city%20of%20Gezer.)%20He%20also%20built%20up%20the%20towns%20of%20Lower%20Beth-horon%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EBaalath%2C%20and%20Tamar%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E9%3A18%3C%2Fspan%3E%20An%20alternate%20reading%20in%20the%20Masoretic%20Text%20reads%20%3Cem%3ETadmor.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20the%20wilderness%20within%20his%20land.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_19%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20built%20towns%20as%20supply%20centers%20and%20constructed%20towns%20where%20his%20chariots%20and%20horses%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E9%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Eand%20charioteers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20could%20be%20stationed.%20He%20built%20everything%20he%20desired%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20Lebanon%20and%20throughout%20his%20entire%20realm.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_20%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20were%20still%20some%20people%20living%20in%20the%20land%20who%20were%20not%20Israelites%2C%20including%20Amorites%2C%20Hittites%2C%20Perizzites%2C%20Hivites%2C%20and%20Jebusites.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_21%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20were%20descendants%20of%20the%20nations%20whom%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20had%20not%20completely%20destroyed.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E9%3A21%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20Hebrew%20term%20used%20here%20refers%20to%20the%20complete%20consecration%20of%20things%20or%20people%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20either%20by%20destroying%20them%20or%20by%20giving%20them%20as%20an%20offering.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20So%20Solomon%20conscripted%20them%20as%20slaves%2C%20and%20they%20serve%20as%20forced%20laborers%20to%20this%20day.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_22%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Solomon%20did%20not%20conscript%20any%20of%20the%20Israelites%20for%20forced%20labor.%20Instead%2C%20he%20assigned%20them%20to%20serve%20as%20fighting%20men%2C%20government%20officials%2C%20officers%20and%20captains%20in%20his%20army%2C%20commanders%20of%20his%20chariots%2C%20and%20charioteers.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_23%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3ESolomon%20appointed%20550%26%23xA0%3Bof%20them%20to%20supervise%20the%20people%20working%20on%20his%20various%20projects.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_9_24%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3ESolomon%20moved%20his%20wife%2C%20Pharaoh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20daughter%2C%20from%20the%20City%20of%20David%20to%20the%20new%20palace%20he%20had%20built%20for%20her.%20Then%20he%20constructed%20the%20supporting%20terraces.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20or